text: Knockoura () is a mountain in County Cork, Ireland. == Geography == At an elevation of 490 metres Knockoura is one of the Irish Hangliding & Paragliding (IHPA)IHPA website ihpa.ie sites as well as being a site for 4 communications masts for telephone, TV, VHF, coastguard and WiMax antennas == References == == See also == * List of Marilyns in Ireland Category:Mountains and hills of County Cork Category:Marilyns of Ireland
title: Knockoura
